CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 27, 1957, pg. A24 reads: "Alphas A La Trinidad - In keeping with their theme, "Calypso Carnival," the members of the Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity greeted guests at their annual outing at North Park Lodge Friday, in colorful West Indian garb. First row, left to right: Charles Angell, Dennis Goggins and John Cundeiff.  Second row: Wendell Stanton, the small son of the Rev. Leroy Patrick, Howard Cuthbert.  Last row: Forrest Parr, Dr. Charles Cephas, the Rev. Leroy Patrick, Morris Fountain, William Leftridge and Dr. Robert Bolden. - Teenie Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Alpha Phi Alpha fraternity members, first row from left: Charles Angell, Dennis Goggins, John Cundeiff; second row: Wendell Stanton, son of LeRoy Patrick, Howard Cuthbert; last row: Forrest Parr, Dr. Charles Cephas, Rev. LeRoy Patrick, Morris Fountain Sr., William Leftridge, and Dr. Robert Bolden wearing West Indian style costumes for "Calypso Carnival," North Park
